{"id":136071,"name":"Interactive Media Community Group","is_closed":false,"description":"<p>The Interactive Media Community Group is interested in all forms of interactive media, e.g., <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interactive_storytelling\" target=\"_blank\">interactive storytelling</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamebook\" target=\"_blank\">digital gamebooks</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_comic\" target=\"_blank\">motion comics</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_novel\" target=\"_blank\">visual novels</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interactive_film\" target=\"_blank\">interactive films</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypervideo\" target=\"_blank\">hypervideo</a>, and <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serious_game\" target=\"_blank\">serious games</a>.</p>\r\n<p>This Group considers and discusses how standardization can support all forms of interactive media. This Group may work on a number of deliverables, reports, and specifications.</p>\r\n","shortname":"interactive-media","discr":"w3cgroup","type":"community group","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.w3.org/groups/cg/interactive-media"},"homepage":{"href":"https://www.w3.org/community/interactive-media/"},"users":{"href":"https://api.w3.org/groups/cg/interactive-media/users"},"services":{"href":"https://api.w3.org/groups/cg/interactive-media/services"},"chairs":{"href":"https://api.w3.org/groups/cg/interactive-media/chairs"},"join":{"href":"https://www.w3.org/community/interactive-media/join"},"participations":{"href":"https://api.w3.org/groups/cg/interactive-media/participations"}},"identifier":"cg/interactive-media"}